images.caption: Figure 3:Visual comparisons between FLUX and 1.58-bit FLUX on GenEval dataset.1.58-bit FLUX demonstrates comparable generation quality to FLUX while employing 1.58-bit quantization, where 99.5% of the 11.9B parameters in the vision transformer are constrained to the values +1, -1, or 0. For consistency, all images in each comparison are generated using the same latent noise input. 1.58-bit FLUX utilizes a custom 1.58-bit kernel.
